        "content": "A syllogism is a three-part argument containing two premises and one conclusion. Example: 'All mammals breathe air. Whales are mammals. Therefore, whales breathe air.' This format, refined by Aristotle, is the original machine of reasoning. Every modern proof, debate, or computer algorithm is a descendant of this simple structure—a quiet reminder that logic’s roots run deep and ancient."
      },
