        "content": "Validity measures whether an argument’s structure guarantees its conclusion. If the form prevents truth from leaking out, the argument is valid. Validity doesn’t ask if the premises are true—it asks if, *given* the premises, the conclusion must follow. Think of it as testing a bridge with blueprints, not traffic. You inspect design first; the material check comes later."
      },
