      "content": "Categorical syllogisms deal with classes of things—'All,' 'Some,' 'None.' They teach how inclusion and exclusion shape reasoning. 'All poets are dreamers. Some dreamers are realists. Therefore, some poets may be realists.' Within this pattern, every word matters. Swap 'all' for 'most' and you change the universe. Deduction teaches linguistic precision—how tiny shifts in language reshape logical space."
