      "content": "Formal fallacies break the skeleton of logic. They aren’t emotional tricks; they’re structural errors. 'If A then B. B, therefore A' (affirming the consequent) looks clean but sneaks in reversal. 'If A then B. Not A, therefore not B' (denying the antecedent) leaves open possibilities it pretends are closed. Deduction collapses when sequence is disrespected."
