      "id": "2.4.49",
      "title": "Beyond Winning",
      "content": "Arguments aren’t battles to win but puzzles to solve together. Soundness shifts focus from victory to clarity. When both sides refine their reasoning, everyone wins something deeper—mutual respect and shared illumination. The best outcome of logic is understanding, not triumph."
    },
    {
      "id": "2.4.50",
      "title": "Intellectual Virtue",
      "content": "Sound reasoning cultivates intellectual virtue: patience, humility, courage, fairness. These traits outlast any single debate. They turn thinking into character. The true measure of logic isn’t how many arguments you win—it’s how much wisdom you carry into the next one."
